description.narrative:
Output 1- Improved municipal resilience through increased capacity for waste management, clean water and electricity supply including the provision of technical support, equipment, works and training 

Baseline: Municipal services unable to cope with migration crisis; 
Indicators:Level of Improved waste collection and processing capacities in 2 municipalities
Level of Improved water supply and water quality in 2 municipalities

Output 2 - Increased community mobilization leads to increased social cohesion and resilience
Baseline: Low participation of local community in crisis response efforts; No conflict mediation capacities;
Indicators: Strengthened capacities of 10 local CSOs to play role in response efforts; 
Improved  social cohesion in society through number of conducted local level activities;


Output 3 - National and local level crisis response coordination mechanisms strengthened and institutionalized

Baseline: Insufficient coordination between national and local level response; Ad-hoc mechanisms in place;

Indicators: Increased level of coordination among institutions for crisis response
Improved mechanisms for coordination and crisis response

